<SP>
<SPEAKER>Har.</SPEAKER>
<P>"I have told her the truth. She knows all: knows what a vile infernal&mdash;I tell you &s;he knows me! My father again &s;hall look upon <Q>the glare of the day! Fir&s;t to the proctor, next to the lawyer, and then&mdash;! Ha, ha, ha! Ay then to my fair bride! Heare&s;t thou, my noble &s;oul? I &s;ay my bride! My fair, my bloom|ing, thrice-bedded bride! No novice &s;he, old true blue! Tol de rol&mdash;It will be a merry wedding! Con|&s;ole my father! Cheer him! Enlighten his &s;oul with hope! I'll keep my word; What, does he not know me? Am I not his own &s;on?</Q>&mdash;Why, ay&mdash; <STAGE>[Looking at his watch]</STAGE> The proctor's, the lawyer's, the widow's, and <STAGE>[Starts]</STAGE> at &s;ix?&mdash; <STAGE>[A&s;ide]</STAGE> The Ring?&mdash;The Ring at &s;ix? Fiends!&mdash;Who can &s;ay what may happen?&mdash;What, leave my father to peri&s;h?&mdash;I'll not go! Though all hell &s;hould brand me for a coward, I'll not go!&mdash;Mr. Smith, take care of my father!&mdash;Mark me, I recommend my father to you! <STAGE>[Exit.</STAGE></P>
